@JohnWFir years  I've used a little accessory called a "pen loop."  It attaches a pen to the back of your hand so that it's always available; you can flip it into your hand with a quick gesture, but the rest of the time both hands are free. I started using it when I worked in warehouses. 

They were invented for pilots, so that they could have a pen instantly at hand without having to scrounge around for it with one hand off the controls. 

Would I object to someone referring to it as something used by pilots? No, of course not, even though I'm not a pilot, and even though I know of a few other non-pilots who've started using them.

